        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 6:29AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 628 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Fordtran, or 15 miles southeast of Yoakum, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
El Campo, Columbus, Sheridan, Cordele, Altair, Nada, Morales,
Garwood, Rock Island, and Louise.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
